[h2 id=Planning 
	" Planning
	$LF
]h2
[h3 id=SelectYourGame 
	" Select your game
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Game choice is not critical whatsoever in terms of submissions to TASVideos. You are free to TAS any game you like. What matters most is choosing something that you enjoy, and that will keep you motivated throughout. Games that you personally enjoy, or games that you already know very well, are great choices for beginners to TASing. Games with active TASing communities can also be a great choice for beginners, as information is plentiful and direct help is never far away.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=SelectYourGoal 
	" Select your goal
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"This is generally fastest completion, or "any%", for most games, though there are a wide variety of other goals you can choose. 
	(__wikiLink|href=/MovieTagGuidelines|implicitdisplaytext=Movie Tag Guidelines)
	" contains a list of goals we currently officially support, though keep in mind this is a growing list, and that 
	[em 
		"any
	]em
	" goal can be acceptable.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Goals should be clear, objective, and attainable. Always stay within your goals: If you are doing an "all items" run, you must obtain all items. If your game has infinitely respawning enemies, you should not be aiming for a goal like "100% kills".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"You are permitted to trade off speed for entertainment, if you want to. Just make sure to make note in the submission description exactly what trade-offs you made, to clarify to a judge whether a particular speed loss is a deliberate choice instead of just being a mistake.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=DoResearch 
	" Do research
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"The first thing you should do is 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Search|implicitdisplaytext=search)
	" our submissions and publications to see if we have any finished runs. There may be users on our 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Forum|implicitdisplaytext=Forum)
	" or 
	(__wikiLink|href=/DiscordServer|implicitdisplaytext=Discord Server)
	" that have put time into TASing your chosen game. Outside of TASVideos, you may find RTA runs, normal playthroughs, guides, maps, tricks, bugs, memory addresses, or even other TASes that can help you plan and create yours.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Primary resources:
	$LF
]div
